Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. 1:17 PM Prosecuting attorney Jillian Pfeifer in court for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant Dylan James Zettler appeared by video, in custody. Attorney Elizabeth F Svehlek appeared by video for Dylan James Zettler. Calling 22CF149, 22CF149, 22TR1313 & 22TR1314. Svehlek states there are not conflicts and is appointed on both cases. Pfeifer/Svehlek statement to bond in 22CF149.  In receipt of complaint, waive reading - will proceed with preliminary hearing/arraignment today. Court sets bond in 22CF149 and continues bond in 22CF144.  Defendant waives preliminary hearing. Waiver free and voluntary. Court finds that probable cause exists and binds over. Pfeifer states Information will be filed that mirrors Complaint. Svehlek willing to proceed to Arraignment today; waives further reading and enters not guilty pleas. adj. 01:13 PM
Pre-trial conference scheduled for July 26, 2022 at 03:30 pm.

Victim appearing by video. Calling 22CF149, 22CF144, 22TR1313 & 22TR1314. 22CF149 set for initial appearance. Svehlek states will be representing on new case. Svehlek states may have possible conflict in new case - would like to set for an adjourned initial. Court will hold off on setting bond in new case - continues bond in 22CF144.. adj. 03:16 PM
Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for June 29, 2022 at 01:15 pm.
